descript.abstract: This data set is known as Improvement Outdoor Recreation Parks abbreviated PARK_AREA and contains the park boundaries for for the City of Bakersfield, CA.
descript.purpose: This data set was created to aid in local GIS and mapping applications.

sngdate.caldate: REQUIRED: The year (and optionally month, or month and day) for which the data set corresponds to the ground.

horizpa.horizpar:
The best expected accuracy of this data set is +/- 100 feet.
Park boundaries where extracted from CDRELBND with an spatial accuracy of +/- 2 feet. Valley Wide GIS with a spatial accuracy of +/- 107 feet. All parks boundaries with the exception of the Kern River Parkway have been verified to be within +/- 50 feet of GPS tree locations.
